This paper is primarily focused on natural language processing (NLP) and machine translation, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CL (Computation and Language) category. The paper also discusses the use of neural networks and deep learning techniques, which are commonly used in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper evaluates the performance of different components of the NMT model, which could fall under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the use of attention mechanisms, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) but are also increasingly used in NLP.
